  "intent_precise": "7805de-part-2.ot2.apiv2: Using Reagent Reservoir (reservoir, slot 1), mag_plate (pcr_plate, slot Mag Plate), reagent_block (tube_rack, slot 4 Degree Block), RNA Sample Plate on Chilled Aluminum Block (plate, slot 7). With magnetic module, temperature module. (1) Wait 10 seconds. (2) Pause: message (3) Pause for incubation. (4) Pause for incubation. (5) Pause for incubation. (6) Pause for incubation. (7) Transfer from source to destination. (8) Wait 10 seconds. (9) Disengage magnets to release beads. (10) Transfer 2\u00b5L from source (A1, A1) to destination (A1, A1). (11) Distribute 48\u00b5L from source A1 to destination wells A1, A1, A1. (12) Transfer 40\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (13) Mix wells multiple wells in plate, 10 cycles at 55\u00b5L. (14) Incubate for 5 minutes. (15) Engage magnets at engage_offsetmm height for bead separation. (16) Pause for incubation. (17) Wait 1 seconds. (18) Wait 1 seconds. (19) Disengage magnets to release beads. (20) Engage magnets for bead separation. (21) Incubate for 1 minutes. (22) Pause for incubation. (23) Disengage magnets to release beads. (24) Transfer 26\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (25) Incubate for 2 minutes. (26) Engage magnets for bead separation. (27) Pause for incubation. (28) Transfer 25\u00b5L from source to destination.",
  "intent_concise": "Perform distribute to A1, A1, A1, magnetic bead separation. (volumes 2\u00b5L-127\u00b5L, ~10 min total)",
  "intent": "For this RNA extraction protocol, start by setting up your reagent reservoir in slot 1, magnetic plate in the mag plate slot, reagent block in the 4-degree slot, and RNA sample plate on the chilled aluminum block in slot 7. Begin with a 10-second wait, then proceed through the initial incubation pauses before transferring your samples and waiting another 10 seconds. Release the magnetic beads, then carefully transfer 2\u00b5L from A1 to A1, distribute 48\u00b5L from source A1 to three A1 destination wells, and transfer 40\u00b5L from A1 to A1. Mix the wells for 10 cycles at 55\u00b5L volume, incubate for 5 minutes with magnets engaged at the specified offset height, then cycle through the magnetic bead separations with 1-second waits, disengage and re-engage magnets with a 1-minute incubation, transfer 26\u00b5L from A1 to A1, incubate for 2 minutes with magnets engaged, and finish with a 25\u00b5L transfer from source to destination.",
